sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant Gateway as vllm-orchestrator-gateway<br/>8090/TCP HTTP
    participant Orchestrator as FMS Guardrails Orchestrator<br/>8085/TCP HTTP/HTTPS
    participant Detectors as Guardrails Detectors<br/>(e.g., regex-language)
    participant vLLM as vLLM / Model Server

    Note over Client,vLLM: Flow 1: Non-Streaming Chat Completion with Detection

    Client->>Gateway: POST /{route_name}/v1/chat/completions<br/>Authorization: Bearer token<br/>Content-Type: application/json<br/>{"stream": false, "messages": [...]}
    Note over Gateway: Inject detector configs from<br/>route YAML into request payload
    Gateway->>Orchestrator: POST /api/v2/chat/completions-detection<br/>Authorization passthrough<br/>X-Forwarded-* headers<br/>Optional mTLS client cert
    Orchestrator->>Detectors: Run input detectors
    Detectors-->>Orchestrator: Detection results
    Orchestrator->>vLLM: Inference request
    vLLM-->>Orchestrator: Generated completion
    Orchestrator->>Detectors: Run output detectors
    Detectors-->>Orchestrator: Detection results
    Orchestrator-->>Gateway: JSON response with detections field
    Note over Gateway: Check detections:<br/>If found → substitute fallback_message<br/>If none → pass through original
    Gateway-->>Client: JSON response (original or fallback)

    Note over Client,vLLM: Flow 2: Streaming Chat Completion (SSE)

    Client->>Gateway: POST /{route_name}/v1/chat/completions<br/>{"stream": true, "messages": [...]}
    Gateway->>Orchestrator: POST /api/v2/chat/completions-detection<br/>Optional mTLS
    Orchestrator->>vLLM: Streaming inference
    loop SSE chunks
        vLLM-->>Orchestrator: SSE data chunk
        Orchestrator-->>Gateway: SSE data chunk (may include detections)
        Note over Gateway: Parse SSE chunk:<br/>If detection found → replace with fallback
        Gateway-->>Client: SSE data chunk (original or fallback)
    end
    Gateway-->>Client: data: [DONE]

    Note over Client,vLLM: Flow 3: Detection Triggered (Fallback)

    Client->>Gateway: POST /{route_name}/v1/chat/completions
    Gateway->>Orchestrator: POST /api/v2/chat/completions-detection
    Orchestrator-->>Gateway: Response with detections populated
    Note over Gateway: Detections found!<br/>Substitute route's fallback_message<br/>into choices[].message.content
    Gateway-->>Client: Response with fallback_message<br/>(content policy enforced)
